% The Fibonacci sequence is defined by the recurrence relation:
% 
%     F_(n) = F_(n?1) + F_(n?2), where F_(1) = 1 and F_(2) = 1.
% 
% Hence the first 12 terms will be:
% 
%     F_(1) = 1 F_(2) = 1 F_(3) = 2 F_(4) = 3 F_(5) = 5 F_(6) = 8 F_(7) =
%     13 F_(8) = 21 F_(9) = 34 F_(10) = 55 F_(11) = 89 F_(12) = 144
% 
% The 12th term, F_(12), is the first term to contain three digits.
% 
% What is the first term in the Fibonacci sequence to contain 1000 digits?

% F_(n) is equal to rounding the value of phi^n / sqrt(5) , see fib.m

% log_10 x = log x / log 10

% we want log_10 F(n) >= 1000 - 1 = 999

% i.e. log F(n) >= log(10) * 999

% log F(n) is approx log( phi^n / sqrt(5) ) = n log phi - 0.5 log 5

% For very large n, this approximation should be very close.

% Solve n log phi - 0.5 log 5 = log(10) * 999

% i.e n = [ log(10) * 999 + 0.5 log 5 ] / log phi

phi = 0.5 * (1 + sqrt(5));

nApprox = (log(10)*999 + 0.5*log(5)) / log(phi);
nApprox = round(nApprox);

fib(nApprox) == Inf; % in Matlab.

